revision.text:
The '''BWF Grand Prix Gold and Grand Prix''' is a series of badminton tournaments, sanctioned by [[Badminton World Federation]] (BWF) since 2007.
==Features== ===Prize money=== A Grand Prix Gold tournament offers minimum prize money of [[United States dollar|US$]]120,000; a Grand Prix tournament offers minimum prize money of US$50,000. The formula of prize money distribution is identical to [[BWF Super Series#Prize money|Super Series]] tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Regulations for Grand Prix|url=http://www.bwfbadminton.org/file.aspx?id=524497&dl=1|work=Badminton World Federation|publisher=Bwfbadminton.org|accessdate=15 February 2014}}</ref>
===World Ranking points=== {{main|BWF World Ranking}}
The BWF Grand Prix Gold and Grand Prix series offers third only to BWF tournaments (after BWF events and Super Series), according to World Ranking system.<ref>{{cite web|title=Overview Ranking|url=http://www.bwfbadminton.org/page.aspx?id=15370|work=Badminton World Federation|publisher=Bwfbadminton.org|accessdate=15 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110813001214/http://bwfbadminton.org/page.aspx?id=15370|archive-date=2011-08-13|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
