Unlike the other falling diphthongs (that is, falling from higher to lower sonority), {{IPA|/iu/}} and {{IPA|/oi/}} are rising diphthongs. For example, ''kiu'' ('spy') is pronounced {{IPA|[kju]}}, like the English name for the letter ''Q''.

As with its constituent vowels, diphthongs with short {{IPAslink|e}} and {{IPAslink|a}} are subject to the same free variation described above. In rapid speech, {{IPA|/ai/}} and {{IPA|/au/}} can become {{IPA|[ei]}} and {{IPA|[ou]}} respectively.

