'''Die Lesewut''' ([[German language|German]] for the ''reading craze'') or '''Die Lesesucht''' (''reading mania''), are terms that describe a period in [[German history]] beginning in the eighteenth century.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Arthor, Art, and the Market: Rereading the History of Aesthetics |last=Woodmansee |first=Martha |authorlink=Martha Woodmansee |year=1994 |publisher=Columbia University Press |location=New York |isbn=0-231-10601-7 |page=23 }}</ref> [[Johann Wolfgang Goethe|Goethe's]] [[The Sorrows of Young Werther]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/stream/bodotheauthorart00woodrich/bodotheauthorart00woodrich_djvu.txt |title=Novel Content Creation |accessdate=2008-06-25 |last=Galbi |first=Douglas |date=March 18, 2007 |work= |publisher=Purple Motes}}</ref> and the [[Sturm und Drang]] movement are considered to have been the catalyst for this event.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}

